Dear MizzB I’M 28 and have been staying with my boyfriend after moving out of home, as my parents don’t like my lover. But he’s changed and brings women to our room and sleeps with them in front of me. I tried talking to him, but he threatens to kick me out. ) Sister Hey Sister, When you get into a relationship, it’s helpful to do so with a clear picture of what you expect from your partner. Disrespect is in no way a loving or caring, but your family always has your back. You can apologise to your parents and move back home. Learn to love and value yourself, so the person who comes into your life does the same. You can send a Please Call Me to 083 323 1023 to speak to a counsellor.